aVthis is a great summertime place.  i have been going to rolands since i turned 21 a decade ago.   the beer selection is one of the best in pittsburgh if not the best.  and, i agree with jason p. in that the best sandwich in the burgh is the lobster roll.  i prefer the cold lobster roll as opposed to the hot, but they are both awesome.  it's a very generous portion of lobster on a garlic bread roll.  they have a very good raw bar with oysters, shrimp, crab and other goodies.  the outdoor seating is awesome.  sit upstairs and look at the passerby's on the street at the strip.  saturday's and sunday's afternoon are the best time to visit.  the pizza is also pretty good, brick oven and thin crust.  the seafood stew is a great deal for about $15 you get a delicious broth and lots of fish and shellfish.  the bartenders are great.  it's pretty well known that john the irish guy is the best bartender in the burgh', however i think he only works one day a week now.  bo is very good and my buddy jeff is also a good tender.   they have pool tables and darts, so plenty of bar games.  the only reason i don't give this place four stars is that they don't have all the top shelf liquor that my heart desires.  they have new management since my buddy rick went to bettis bar.  and, they are lacking in some liquor selections since.  they don't have patron or any top shelf rum.  i ordered a top shelf long island iced tea yesterday and was disappointed to taste cuervo instead of petrone.   however, overall the place is a good time and a must visit in pittsburgh.  get the lobster roll!
