aVi eat at the harris grill at least once a week.  \u000a\u000atheir beer list is huge, the food is good, and with the exception of one server the service is fantastic.  if you go, see if you can sit in justin's section.  \u000a\u000athe harris is one of the few bars in pittsburgh open late night if you're looking for food.  while most area kitchens close at 11, the harris is open and serving until 1 am--full menu!\u000a\u000atuesday is bacon night and if you go for happy hour get there early, or be prepared to wait.  bacon and beer are fantastic together until you have that moment where you realized, "i've just had 15 pieces of bacon."  order another beer, you'll feel better about yourself.\u000a\u000apeople rave about the frozen cosmos and they're ok but not really my thing.  try the drink with the muddled cucumbers--it is fantastic.  \u000a\u000athey also have a good sunday brunch.  in the summer months its a buffet which i dont like as much as the regular, menu style brunch they have in colder months.  bloody mary's are half off after 2pm, so i often like to work out in the morning and then spend the afternoon having a "sunday funday."\u000a\u000athe food at the harris is generally good, but they change their menu a lot and while that can be a good thing i've found it frustrating as several of my favorite menu items ie shawshank redemption and the crawful of falaffel are no longer offered.  the food is somewhat consistent, although sometimes it is over seasoned.  i ordered the meatloaf once and it had so much rosemary in it i found it almost inedible--although my boyfriend tried it and loved it.  the delmonico a go go is so fatty i don't recommend it.  it's a good sandwich, but it owuld be better if they made it with different/better meat.  several times i've gone to order a menu item and they're out of it.  the staff is usually pretty good about letting you know what's off the menu ahead of time but sometimes you want to ask.\u000a\u000awhat the harris does well they do fantastic.  the lasagna, the burgers, the greek salad, the gazpacho, the fish tacos, the steak, the hummus-- all excellent.  try the gazpacho, it's excellent!\u000a\u000athe staff is fantastic.  i think the harris has the best bartenders in town.  if you get to know them, they'll take fantastic care of you.  even if htey don't know you, you can expect to get your drinks quickly, and your cocktails mixed correctly.\u000a\u000athis place can get expensive.  if you're drinking craft beers be careful bc your bill can creep up on you quickly.  it is, in my opinion, priced right for what you are getting.\u000a\u000athis is my favorite bar in pittsburgh and i hope you check it out if you havne't yet.  wait for the patio, it's worth it!
